{"paragraphs":[{"cues":[{"time":110,"text":"I'm a veteran of the starship Enterprise."},{"time":4539,"text":"I soared through the galaxy"},{"time":7899,"text":"driving a huge starship"},{"time":10635,"text":"with a crew made up of people"},{"time":12034,"text":"from all over this world,"},{"time":14970,"text":"many different races, many different cultures,"},{"time":18420,"text":"many different heritages,"},{"time":20264,"text":"all working together,"},{"time":22221,"text":"and our mission was to explore strange new worlds,"},{"time":25866,"text":"to seek out new life and new civilizations,"},{"time":29742,"text":"to boldly go where no one has gone before."}]},{"cues":[{"time":34705,"text":"Well —"},{"time":36190,"text":"(Applause) —"},{"time":42906,"text":"I am the grandson of immigrants from Japan"},{"time":47561,"text":"who went to America,"},{"time":49692,"text":"boldly going to a strange new world,"},{"time":53177,"text":"seeking new opportunities."},{"time":56013,"text":"My mother was born in Sacramento, California."},{"time":59499,"text":"My father was a San Franciscan."},{"time":61940,"text":"They met and married in Los Angeles,"},{"time":64685,"text":"and I was born there."}]},{"cues":[{"time":68406,"text":"I was four years old"},{"time":70659,"text":"when Pearl Harbor was bombed"},{"time":72489,"text":"on December 7, 1941 by Japan,"},{"time":77231,"text":"and overnight, the world was plunged"},{"time":81240,"text":"into a world war."},{"time":84674,"text":"America suddenly was swept up"},{"time":87627,"text":"by hysteria."},{"time":91551,"text":"Japanese-Americans,"},{"time":93025,"text":"American citizens of Japanese ancestry,"},{"time":96185,"text":"were looked on"},{"time":97520,"text":"with suspicion and fear"},{"time":101542,"text":"and with outright hatred"},{"time":104514,"text":"simply because we happened to look like"},{"time":107174,"text":"the people that bombed Pearl Harbor."},{"time":109870,"text":"And the hysteria grew and grew"},{"time":113340,"text":"until in February 1942,"},{"time":116930,"text":"the president of the United States,"},{"time":119074,"text":"Franklin Delano Roosevelt,"},{"time":121244,"text":"ordered all Japanese-Americans"},{"time":123917,"text":"on the West Coast of America"},{"time":126026,"text":"to be summarily rounded up"},{"time":128942,"text":"with no charges, with no trial,"},{"time":132147,"text":"with no due process."},{"time":134574,"text":"Due process, this is a core pillar"},{"time":137165,"text":"of our justice system."},{"time":138778,"text":"That all disappeared."},{"time":141207,"text":"We were to be rounded up"},{"time":143306,"text":"and imprisoned in 10 barbed-wire prison camps"},{"time":147567,"text":"in some of the most desolate places in America:"},{"time":151759,"text":"the blistering hot desert of Arizona,"},{"time":155186,"text":"the sultry swamps of Arkansas,"},{"time":158651,"text":"the wastelands of Wyoming, Idaho, Utah, Colorado,"},{"time":162344,"text":"and two of the most desolate places in California."}]},{"cues":[{"time":167778,"text":"On April 20th, I celebrated my fifth birthday,"},{"time":172546,"text":"and just a few weeks after my birthday,"},{"time":176163,"text":"my parents got my younger brother,"},{"time":178934,"text":"my baby sister and me"},{"time":180992,"text":"up very early one morning,"},{"time":183021,"text":"and they dressed us hurriedly."},{"time":186246,"text":"My brother and I were in the living room"},{"time":188240,"text":"looking out the front window,"},{"time":191303,"text":"and we saw two soldiers marching up our driveway."},{"time":195147,"text":"They carried bayonets on their rifles."},{"time":199669,"text":"They stomped up the front porch"},{"time":202470,"text":"and banged on the door."},{"time":204989,"text":"My father answered it,"},{"time":207094,"text":"and the soldiers ordered us out of our home."},{"time":211835,"text":"My father gave my brother and me"},{"time":214160,"text":"small luggages to carry,"},{"time":215902,"text":"and we walked out and stood on the driveway"},{"time":219418,"text":"waiting for our mother to come out,"},{"time":222413,"text":"and when my mother finally came out,"},{"time":225728,"text":"she had our baby sister in one arm,"},{"time":228791,"text":"a huge duffel bag in the other,"},{"time":232163,"text":"and tears were streaming down both her cheeks."},{"time":237305,"text":"I will never be able to forget that scene."},{"time":241092,"text":"It is burned into my memory."}]},{"cues":[{"time":245440,"text":"We were taken from our home"},{"time":248231,"text":"and loaded on to train cars"},{"time":250749,"text":"with other Japanese-American families."},{"time":253759,"text":"There were guards stationed"},{"time":255239,"text":"at both ends of each car,"},{"time":258699,"text":"as if we were criminals."},{"time":261398,"text":"We were taken two thirds of\nthe way across the country,"},{"time":265555,"text":"rocking on that train for four days and three nights,"},{"time":269767,"text":"to the swamps of Arkansas."},{"time":273502,"text":"I still remember the barbed wire fence"},{"time":275515,"text":"that confined me."},{"time":278125,"text":"I remember the tall sentry tower"},{"time":280712,"text":"with the machine guns pointed at us."},{"time":284965,"text":"I remember the searchlight that followed me"},{"time":287654,"text":"when I made the night runs"},{"time":289093,"text":"from my barrack to the latrine."},{"time":292344,"text":"But to five-year-old me,"},{"time":294504,"text":"I thought it was kind of nice that they'd lit the way"},{"time":296800,"text":"for me to pee."},{"time":300054,"text":"I was a child,"},{"time":301947,"text":"too young to understand the circumstances"},{"time":304572,"text":"of my being there."}]},{"cues":[{"time":307003,"text":"Children are amazingly adaptable."},{"time":311769,"text":"What would be grotesquely abnormal"},{"time":315326,"text":"became my normality"},{"time":318180,"text":"in the prisoner of war camps."},{"time":321794,"text":"It became routine for me to line up three times a day"},{"time":325484,"text":"to eat lousy food in a noisy mess hall."},{"time":330231,"text":"It became normal for me to go with my father"},{"time":332436,"text":"to bathe in a mass shower."},{"time":335384,"text":"Being in a prison, a barbed-wire prison camp,"},{"time":339645,"text":"became my normality."}]},{"cues":[{"time":343269,"text":"When the war ended,"},{"time":344910,"text":"we were released,"},{"time":346962,"text":"and given a one-way ticket"},{"time":348968,"text":"to anywhere in the United States."},{"time":352534,"text":"My parents decided to go back home"},{"time":354435,"text":"to Los Angeles,"},{"time":357003,"text":"but Los Angeles was not a welcoming place."},{"time":361384,"text":"We were penniless."},{"time":362780,"text":"Everything had been taken from us,"},{"time":365256,"text":"and the hostility was intense."},{"time":367689,"text":"Our first home was on Skid Row"},{"time":370540,"text":"in the lowest part of our city,"},{"time":375493,"text":"living with derelicts, drunkards"},{"time":378060,"text":"and crazy people,"},{"time":380080,"text":"the stench of urine all over,"},{"time":382674,"text":"on the street, in the alley,"},{"time":385787,"text":"in the hallway."},{"time":388108,"text":"It was a horrible experience,"},{"time":390810,"text":"and for us kids, it was terrorizing."},{"time":394226,"text":"I remember once"},{"time":396738,"text":"a drunkard came staggering down,"},{"time":399690,"text":"fell down right in front of us,"},{"time":402207,"text":"and threw up."},{"time":403857,"text":"My baby sister said, \"Mama, let's go back home,\""},{"time":409174,"text":"because behind barbed wires"},{"time":411480,"text":"was for us"},{"time":414096,"text":"home."}]},{"cues":[{"time":416939,"text":"My parents worked hard"},{"time":418590,"text":"to get back on their feet."},{"time":420547,"text":"We had lost everything."},{"time":421666,"text":"They were at the middle of their lives"},{"time":424170,"text":"and starting all over."},{"time":425805,"text":"They worked their fingers to the bone,"},{"time":428354,"text":"and ultimately they were able"},{"time":431632,"text":"to get the capital together to buy"},{"time":434120,"text":"a three-bedroom home in a nice neighborhood."},{"time":437285,"text":"And I was a teenager,"},{"time":438876,"text":"and I became very curious"},{"time":440670,"text":"about my childhood imprisonment."},{"time":443940,"text":"I had read civics books that told me about"},{"time":446980,"text":"the ideals of American democracy."},{"time":450691,"text":"All men are created equal,"},{"time":453356,"text":"we have an inalienable right"},{"time":456267,"text":"to life, liberty and the pursuit of happiness,"},{"time":461206,"text":"and I couldn't quite make that fit"},{"time":463440,"text":"with what I knew to be my childhood imprisonment."},{"time":466829,"text":"I read history books,"},{"time":468910,"text":"and I couldn't find anything about it."},{"time":471781,"text":"And so I engaged my father after dinner"},{"time":475685,"text":"in long, sometimes heated conversations."},{"time":480245,"text":"We had many, many conversations like that,"},{"time":483013,"text":"and what I got from them"},{"time":485792,"text":"was my father's wisdom."},{"time":487982,"text":"He was the one that suffered the most"},{"time":490294,"text":"under those conditions of imprisonment,"},{"time":493760,"text":"and yet he understood American democracy."},{"time":497737,"text":"He told me that our democracy"},{"time":500464,"text":"is a people's democracy,"},{"time":502571,"text":"and it can be as great as the people can be,"},{"time":505630,"text":"but it is also as fallible as people are."},{"time":510821,"text":"He told me that American democracy"},{"time":513081,"text":"is vitally dependent on good people"},{"time":517077,"text":"who cherish the ideals of our system"},{"time":521048,"text":"and actively engage in the process"},{"time":524548,"text":"of making our democracy work."},{"time":527278,"text":"And he took me to a campaign headquarters —"},{"time":531343,"text":"the governor of Illinois was\nrunning for the presidency —"},{"time":535134,"text":"and introduced me to American electoral politics."},{"time":539822,"text":"And he also told me about"},{"time":542183,"text":"young Japanese-Americans"},{"time":543961,"text":"during the Second World War."}]},{"cues":[{"time":547021,"text":"When Pearl Harbor was bombed,"},{"time":549825,"text":"young Japanese-Americans,\nlike all young Americans,"},{"time":552806,"text":"rushed to their draft board"},{"time":555304,"text":"to volunteer to fight for our country."},{"time":558712,"text":"That act of patriotism"},{"time":561144,"text":"was answered with a slap in the face."},{"time":565462,"text":"We were denied service,"},{"time":568466,"text":"and categorized as enemy non-alien."},{"time":574328,"text":"It was outrageous to be called an enemy"},{"time":577372,"text":"when you're volunteering to fight for your country,"},{"time":580590,"text":"but that was compounded with the word \"non-alien,\""},{"time":584960,"text":"which is a word that means"},{"time":588070,"text":"\"citizen\" in the negative."},{"time":592111,"text":"They even took the word \"citizen\" away from us,"},{"time":595761,"text":"and imprisoned them for a whole year."}]},{"cues":[{"time":600389,"text":"And then the government realized"},{"time":602377,"text":"that there's a wartime manpower shortage,"},{"time":606747,"text":"and as suddenly as they'd rounded us up,"},{"time":611126,"text":"they opened up the military for service"},{"time":613253,"text":"by young Japanese-Americans."},{"time":616171,"text":"It was totally irrational,"},{"time":618838,"text":"but the amazing thing,"},{"time":621072,"text":"the astounding thing,"},{"time":623429,"text":"is that thousands of young"},{"time":625382,"text":"Japanese-American men and women"},{"time":628340,"text":"again went from behind those barbed-wire fences,"},{"time":632303,"text":"put on the same uniform as that of our guards,"},{"time":635760,"text":"leaving their families in imprisonment,"},{"time":639288,"text":"to fight for this country."}]},{"cues":[{"time":641602,"text":"They said that they were going to fight"},{"time":643563,"text":"not only to get their families out"},{"time":646829,"text":"from behind those barbed-wire fences,"},{"time":649387,"text":"but because they cherished the very ideal"},{"time":652617,"text":"of what our government stands for,"},{"time":654840,"text":"should stand for,"},{"time":656731,"text":"and that was being abrogated"},{"time":659232,"text":"by what was being done."}]},{"cues":[{"time":663145,"text":"All men are created equal."},{"time":665479,"text":"And they went to fight for this country."},{"time":669300,"text":"They were put into a segregated"},{"time":670980,"text":"all Japanese-American unit"},{"time":673202,"text":"and sent to the battlefields of Europe,"},{"time":675826,"text":"and they threw themselves into it."},{"time":678897,"text":"They fought with amazing,"},{"time":681742,"text":"incredible courage and valor."},{"time":685200,"text":"They were sent out on the most dangerous missions"},{"time":688962,"text":"and they sustained the highest combat casualty rate"},{"time":691843,"text":"of any unit proportionally."}]},{"cues":[{"time":695649,"text":"There is one battle that illustrates that."},{"time":698944,"text":"It was a battle for the Gothic Line."},{"time":701988,"text":"The Germans were embedded"},{"time":704290,"text":"in this mountain hillside,"},{"time":706877,"text":"rocky hillside,"},{"time":708449,"text":"in impregnable caves,"},{"time":710929,"text":"and three allied battalions"},{"time":714200,"text":"had been pounding away at it"},{"time":715978,"text":"for six months,"},{"time":717462,"text":"and they were stalemated."},{"time":719892,"text":"The 442nd was called in"},{"time":722786,"text":"to add to the fight,"},{"time":726108,"text":"but the men of the 442nd"},{"time":728274,"text":"came up with a unique"},{"time":731434,"text":"but dangerous idea:"},{"time":733734,"text":"The backside of the mountain"},{"time":735529,"text":"was a sheer rock cliff."},{"time":738190,"text":"The Germans thought an attack from the backside"},{"time":741599,"text":"would be impossible."},{"time":744109,"text":"The men of the 442nd decided to do the impossible."},{"time":748480,"text":"On a dark, moonless night,"},{"time":752223,"text":"they began scaling that rock wall,"},{"time":756471,"text":"a drop of more than 1,000 feet,"},{"time":760090,"text":"in full combat gear."},{"time":762737,"text":"They climbed all night long"},{"time":765581,"text":"on that sheer cliff."},{"time":770279,"text":"In the darkness,"},{"time":772232,"text":"some lost their handhold"},{"time":774312,"text":"or their footing"},{"time":775925,"text":"and they fell to their deaths"},{"time":778122,"text":"in the ravine below."},{"time":780203,"text":"They all fell silently."},{"time":784630,"text":"Not a single one cried out,"},{"time":787195,"text":"so as not to give their position away."},{"time":790427,"text":"The men climbed for eight hours straight,"},{"time":794285,"text":"and those who made it to the top"},{"time":797404,"text":"stayed there until the first break of light,"},{"time":801886,"text":"and as soon as light broke,"},{"time":804965,"text":"they attacked."},{"time":806558,"text":"The Germans were surprised,"},{"time":808212,"text":"and they took the hill"},{"time":809960,"text":"and broke the Gothic Line."},{"time":812970,"text":"A six-month stalemate"},{"time":815258,"text":"was broken by the 442nd"},{"time":817463,"text":"in 32 minutes."}]},{"cues":[{"time":820444,"text":"It was an amazing act,"},{"time":824080,"text":"and when the war ended,"},{"time":826930,"text":"the 442nd returned to the United States"},{"time":830147,"text":"as the most decorated unit"},{"time":832563,"text":"of the entire Second World War."},{"time":835480,"text":"They were greeted back on the White House Lawn"},{"time":838210,"text":"by President Truman, who said to them,"},{"time":840816,"text":"\"You fought not only the enemy"},{"time":844074,"text":"but prejudice, and you won.\""}]},{"cues":[{"time":848694,"text":"They are my heroes."},{"time":852290,"text":"They clung to their belief"},{"time":855337,"text":"in the shining ideals of this country,"},{"time":858389,"text":"and they proved that being an American"},{"time":862680,"text":"is not just for some people,"},{"time":865890,"text":"that race is not how we define being an American."},{"time":871323,"text":"They expanded what it means to be an American,"},{"time":874900,"text":"including Japanese-Americans"},{"time":877224,"text":"that were feared and suspected and hated."},{"time":881398,"text":"They were change agents,"},{"time":884609,"text":"and they left for me"},{"time":887091,"text":"a legacy."},{"time":889308,"text":"They are my heroes"},{"time":891097,"text":"and my father is my hero,"},{"time":893448,"text":"who understood democracy"},{"time":895258,"text":"and guided me through it."},{"time":899329,"text":"They gave me a legacy,"},{"time":901819,"text":"and with that legacy comes a responsibility,"},{"time":905181,"text":"and I am dedicated"},{"time":907597,"text":"to making my country"},{"time":909586,"text":"an even better America,"},{"time":912790,"text":"to making our government"},{"time":915000,"text":"an even truer democracy,"},{"time":918497,"text":"and because of the heroes that I have"},{"time":922237,"text":"and the struggles that we've gone through,"},{"time":925859,"text":"I can stand before you"},{"time":927858,"text":"as a gay Japanese-American,"},{"time":930717,"text":"but even more than that,"},{"time":933184,"text":"I am a proud American."}]},{"cues":[{"time":937192,"text":"Thank you very much."}]},{"cues":[{"time":939379,"text":"(Applause)"}]}]}